==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Phonotypy
<hw>Pho*not"y*py</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A method of
phonetic printing of the English language, as devised by <person>Mr.
Pitman</person>, in which nearly all the ordinary letters and many new
forms are employed in order to indicate each elementary sound by a
separate character.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>phony</ent>⟦br⟧
